title: [Teorainn Dale, Yew Wood]
description: The trail winds lazily through this pleasant copse of yew trees.  Tiny wildflowers, their petals tightly closed, are visible in the moonlight.  Although hidden by the underbrush a mild, nut-like scent informs you that mushrooms grow nearby.

The trail winds lazily through this pleasant copse of yew trees.  Tiny wildflowers turn their faces to the sun.  Although hidden by the underbrush a mild, nut-like scent informs you that mushrooms grow nearby.
